(en) Gusum from above 1933. The resort is mainly known for its iron and brass use with dating back to the 16th century. At the time of the picture and for another time the mill was the completely dominant industry in the resort and offered a large part of the community’s inhabitants jobs. In a bend of Gusumsån, the mill yard was unembarrassed with a function as a disponent residence and a mill office. In 1995, the main building was destroyed in a devastating fire.
The photograph is a contact-copied work material that does not make the airline’s finished postcard fair - https://www.europeana.eu/item/73/S_OM_photo_OMFA000078. AB Flygtrafik. Östergötlands museum - http://digitaltmuseum.se/021016419432. Public Domain Mark - http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/mark/1.0/
